{
  "stem": "6195.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He, he didn't believe in the Kabbalistic [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] reasoning and studying.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he, he was forever studying the Torah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remember, I asked my father once-- because he slept till 12 o'clock, midnight, and so did my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then he used to get up and go to his study and pulled out from that huge library, his-- the Mishnah and this and that-- the parts of the Torah.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And once, like a silly girl, I asked, Father, how is it that you forever, as far as I can remember, you always study in the afternoon and then at night?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You must know it by heart.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father said, you know, the more you learn, the more you found-- find out how little you know.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And yes, that's true, too.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was showing me how it, it deals with, with not only religion as such, it deals with every subject-- with hygiene, and medicine, and, and mathematics.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he, he knew how to combine the religion with knowledge.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not only-- German and Polish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Polish was not so rich, but mainly the Hebrew and German, because my parents were born and raised under the Austro-Hungarian [? emporium. ?] So they attended German schools, of course.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My parents spoke either German, or Yiddish, or Polish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Between themselves, they didn't speak Polish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I spoke to my father in Polish and to my mother in Polish.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If I ever had a problem with an expression when I was doing an essay, it was my father, the highest authority.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He wouldn't rest until he found in the lexicon or the dictionary the right answer for it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So to, to me, he was absolutely the highest authority.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
